headlines.title: An unrestrained Trump defends deploying military to Los Angeles during Fort Bragg visit
headlines.description: When President Donald Trump returned from a Bastille Day visit to Paris during his first term, he asked his military brass to organize a parade akin to the one he’d watched march down the Champs-Élysées.

headlines.title: Trump tax bill could raise taxes on foreign companies
headlines.description: President Donald Trump likes to say he’s bringing in trillions of dollars in investments from foreign countries.

headlines.title: Aaron Rodgers joins Steelers, says it was them or not play
headlines.description: Aaron Rodgers called continuing his playing career with the Steelers a decision that was "best for my soul," and noted that coach Mike Tomlin was the biggest draw when it came to picking Pittsburgh.

headlines.title: LA Immigration Protests Live Updates: Growing Crowds Gather in Other Cities
headlines.description: A large group was demonstrating outside the federal detention center in downtown Los Angeles, and protests were also planned in Chicago and New York City.

headlines.title: Blake Lively just smoked Justin Baldoni in court. The question is if it will matter.
headlines.description: There’s a reason it doesn’t feel like a victory for the actress.

headlines.title: Trump Treasury Sec. Bessent leaves but U.S.-China trade talks continue
headlines.description: The talks, taking place amid the trade war started by President Donald Trump, are expected to center on U.S. export controls and China's rare-earths exports.

headlines.title: ABC News drops Terry Moran over late-night post attacking Trump and Stephen Miller
headlines.description: The network is parting ways with its veteran correspondent two days after he posted a missive on X calling the president and his deputy chief of staff “world-class haters.”

headlines.title: Lawyers for Kilmar Abrego Garcia say Trump administration’s actions left ‘stain’ on Constitution
headlines.description: Lawyers for Kilmar Abrego Garcia are accusing President Donald Trump's administration of pretending for weeks to be powerless to return him to the United States from El Salvador.

headlines.title: Bond set for immigrant falsely accused of threatening to kill Trump
headlines.description: An immigrant man wrongly accused of threatening to assassinate President Donald Trump can be released from a Wisconsin prison on bond.

headlines.title: 23andMe Customers Did Not Expect Their DNA Data Would Be Sold, Lawsuit Claims
headlines.description: The genetic-testing company, which collected DNA data from users, is for sale in bankruptcy court. Now, 27 states and the District of Columbia oppose selling the data without express consent.
